First Lady Melania Trump joined Barbara Nicklaus, co-founder of the Nicklaus Children’s Health Care Foundation, for a luncheon in New York City. They recognized the advances in pediatric healthcare and announced a new healing garden that will open at Nicklaus Children’s Hospital in the coming months. Mrs. Trump expressed her support for the project and emphasized the importance of children's well-being. She mentioned that the healing garden will offer resources for children's physical, mental, educational, and emotional well-being. Mrs. Trump also expressed her desire to visit Florida when the healing garden is ready to meet the patients and families who will benefit from it.